dotfiles
========

Personal dotfiles + machine setup. Drop-in: works on Fedora (dnf) and
Debian / Raspberry Pi OS (apt), desktop or headless.

Setup
-----

    git clone git@github.com:jpbottaro/dotfiles.git
    cd dotfiles
    ./bootstrap              # auto-detects desktop vs server

    ./bootstrap --server     # force minimal (no GUI apps)
    ./bootstrap --desktop     # force GUI extras
    ./bootstrap link          # only re-create symlinks (no package install)

`bootstrap` installs the packages listed in `packages/` via the machine's
package manager, then symlinks everything under `home/` into `$HOME`. It is
idempotent — re-run any time. Real files it would clobber are saved as `*.bak`.

It also installs Tailscale and enables the daemon on every machine (adding
Tailscale's apt repo on Debian/RPi OS, since Fedora packages it directly). Log
in once per machine with `sudo tailscale up` — that interactive step is manual.

Layout
------

    home/              configs, mirrored into $HOME (home/config/* -> ~/.config/*)
    packages/common    CLI packages installed everywhere
    packages/desktop   GUI apps (Fedora desktop only)
    bootstrap          the installer

Editors
-------

Neovim is the default (`EDITOR=nvim`, `vim` aliased to `nvim`). Its config is
`home/config/nvim` (Lua + lazy.nvim); plugins bootstrap on first launch.
`home/vimrc` is a tiny dependency-free fallback for plain vim.
